result.formatted_address: 9 King St, Tai Hang, Hong Kong
result.name: New Hong Kee

reviews.text:
Actually this is the old Hong Kee next door which moved to the present site due to high rent and renamed itself as New Hong Kee.
It is a long established Congee shop in Tai Hang. All dishes are made to order. The quality of food is ok but I felt it has added msg. in the congee.

It’s worth a visit here to get a hand-made rice dumpling (Zongzi, or 糉子 in Chinese) as Dragon Boat Festival is approaching at New Hong Kee, one of the best and oldest joints in Hong Kong for Cantonese congee, one rice porridge. The Chans have been running the business for almost 40 years and the third generation of the family still prepares everything the traditional way to make sure the flavour being authentic.
The best traditional Chinese  'poorman' breakfast.
My favorite, these old fashion shops are fading fast. Been coming to this place when the old couple was running this place, now its the second generation.
One of very few Dai Pai Dong style restaurant left in HK
